Sazka’s Debt May Rise to $553 Million, Hospodarske Reports

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-04-29T06:57:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/sazka-s-debt-may-rise-to-553-million-hospodarske-reports.html
The total debt of Sazka AS, a
bankrupt Czech lottery operator, may rise to about 9 billion
koruna ($553 million) after registration of claims by PPF Group
NV and KKCG, which hold most of Sazka’s bonds,  Hospodarske
Noviny  reported, citing Milan Tomanek, PPF’s spokesman.  The municipal court had received claims amounting to more
than 4 billion koruna from Sazka creditors as of yesterday, the
newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lenka Ponikelska in
Prague   lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  